- 'young adults' refers to players aged between 20 and 30;
- 'typical financial and performance statistics' refer to the average salary, average percentage of the salary cap, average number of games played, and average minutes played per game;
- 'professional seasons' means the seasons recorded in the seasons table.

sql:
SELECT total_salary_cap
   FROM salary_caps
   WHERE team_id = 0 AND season_id = 1;
